data.meta_description: Oliver was born and raised in Ross County Ohio and was introduced into hunting by his grandfather at age 12.
data.text:
Ollie ParkerBuckeye Land Sales

Ohio Land Pro

740-672-0738

Ollie@BuckeyeLandSales.com

Oliver was born and raised in Ross County, Ohio. His passion for the outdoors started at a young age and has grown immensely over the years, leading him to his career in Real Estate where he specializes in rural properties. Oliver has a great foundation built up in Real Estate related matters, land management, and media production making him a strong choice for marketing your property to its best potential. He stays up to date on current market trends, making sure that his clients are well-informed before deciding on a list price, or writing up an offer. He is very personable and loves meeting new people and forming lasting relationships, even after the sale is over. What sets Oliver apart from the competition when it comes to land is his strong background in hunting and land management. He can easily walk through the entire property and find features that will stand out such as timber species that will bring more value, the layout of the topography, and wildlife sign that someone who doesnât have a passion for the outdoors may overlook.

Oliver has great connections to help you from start to finish throughout the buying and selling process. Whether you are needing a surveyor, lender that specializes in land and construction loans, or a title company, heâs got you covered. Oliver shoots with his professional camera for every property he lists, offering stunning pictures that really show what the land has to offer. He also can create videos to better market your home and property. Combine that with his likeable personality and work ethic and you have yourself an agent you can trust to get the job done.

Outside of his career Oliver is a father of two, Jocelyn and Crew. He is very family oriented and well known in the community. He is an avid bowhunter and works year-round on his properties in Ohio and Kentucky to provide the best wildlife habitat possible. He loves introducing friends and children to the sport of hunting and everything the outdoors has to offer. He also enjoys fitness and wellness, photography, and videography. Oliver is a member of the National Association of Realtors, National Wildlife Turkey Federation, and QDMA.

If you are in the market to buy or sell land, do not hesitate to reach out to Oliver at any time. He would be happy to answer any questions you may have and hopes to one day help 100 people purchase their first property.
